<B><FONT SIZE=+2>QBIC: Query by Image Content</FONT></B>

<P>Developed by IBM
<BR>Extensive use of human computer interaction

<P><FONT SIZE=+1><B>Data</B> <B>Model</B></FONT>

<P><B>Database population</B>

<P>Arbitrary number of image objects are identified by the user using semi-automatic
tool.

<P><B>Feature calculation</B>

<P><B>Image query</B>

<P>The user navigates and refines the query until satisfied.

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Content Similarity Retrieval</FONT></B>

<P><B>Semi-Automatic Object Identification</B>

<P>-more acurate than automatic object identification
<BR>-outlines the object in the image
<BR>-floodfill the local region with the similar pixel

<P><B>Automatic Object Identification</B>

<P>-partition based
<BR>-region-based "Query-by-painting" for color

<P><B>Similarity Measures</B>

<P>All of these are user adjustable.&nbsp; This measure is taken by the
weighted sum of the Euclidean distance.
<UL>
<LI>
<B>Color</B></LI>

<LI>
<B>Texture</B></LI>

<LI>
<B>Shape</B></LI>

<LI>
<B>Scene Sketch</B></LI>
</UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Queries</B> <B>and User Interface</B></FONT>

<P><B>Query by example</B>

<P><B>Direct</B> <B>query:&nbsp; </B>The user specifies the color/shape/texture/sketch
or combination of these.

<P><B>Feature palettes or pickers</B>

<P><B>Query</B> <B>by sketch</B>

<P><B>Query-by-painting</B>

<P><B>Results and Query Refinement</B>

<P>Ranked set of thumnail images that may be browsed.

